---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service | ConfigDev"
  description="ConfigDev Terms of Service: acceptable use, zero-liability disclaimers, and usage rules for our free, 100% client-side developer utilities suite."
>
  <main class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <header class="mb-10 pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 tracking-tight mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-400">Last Updated: June 24, 2026</p>
    
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-justify">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">1. Terms Acceptance Matrix</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or utilizing the localized utility dashboards hosted at ConfigDev ("the Service"), you explicitly acknowledge and agree to comply with these comprehensive Terms of Service. If you do not accept these software provisions, you are restricted from utilizing the underlying configuration calculators, validators, and text parsers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">2. Description of Utilities</h2>
        <p>
          ConfigDev operates as a decentralized, non-account-based platform provisioning web-based software execution tools (including crontab converters, PII scrubbers, network masks indicators, and configuration formatters). All functionalities are distributed strictly as free web utilities for personal or commercial application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">3. Acceptable Use Safeguards</h2>
        <p>
          Because all code transformation engines run locally within your browser context, you preserve complete structural control over your configurations. However, you explicitly agree not to use the interface to craft malicious text expressions, simulate automated resource denials, or reverse-engineer the compilation routines for malicious exploitation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">4. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The layout components, interface frameworks, branding coordinates, and system logic compiling code strings on this platform represent unique proprietary assets or open-source licenses maintained by ConfigDev. You are granted a restricted, revocable license to access the layout tools strictly via normal client terminal interfaces.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">5. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="uppercase font-semibold text-neutral-800 text-xs tracking-wide bg-neutral-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
          The service is deployed on an "as is" and "as available" evaluation baseline without any explicit or structural guarantees of any kind. ConfigDev does not claim that formatting output syntax maps flawlessly across every production Linux kernel environment, server distribution configuration, or validation runtime loop. You carry full end-user verification responsibilities before applying generated configuration structures inside real-world architecture.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">6. Fundamental Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          In no scenario shall ConfigDev, its source maintainers, or technical authors be held accountable for any operational regressions, direct server failures, production file line drops, network configuration collapses, data leakages, or financial resource loss stemming from the use, inability to use, or parsing errors generated by our software dashboards.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">7. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We retain full authority to change these system governance regulations at any moment by refreshing the revision coordinates pinned above. Continued execution of user data models inside this platform constitutes persistent acceptance of updated rulesets.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>